  user_input {
    user_response: "I want to create a progressive web app named \"Quick Aid\". The app should satisfy the following problem statement:\n\"QuickAid \342\200\223 Smart First Aid Assistant\nProblem: In most emergencies, people don\342\200\231t know what immediate steps to take before reaching a hospital.\nSolution: Build a web/app that takes symptoms or emergencies (e.g., \342\200\234burn\342\200\235, \342\200\234choking\342\200\235, \342\200\234fracture\342\200\235) and gives voice-guided first-aid steps instantly.\"\n\nThe user should be able to enter the health problem either through text, voice or can choose from the common emergency issues buttons being displayed on the screen\nThe symptoms entered by the user should me collected and the instant first aid instructions need to be strictly taken from WHO instructions. The instructions generated should be generated in the text format and can turn into voice form if the user clicks on a button.\nThere should be an additional feature of GPS option to find the nearby hospitals by connecting with google-maps\nThe app should use Gemini in the background but should generate the first aid instructions only from WHO.\nProvide me fresh code for this such that I can run it in VS code in my laptop\nTry to keep the theme in blue color and a minimalist user interface with clean, responsive design components.\n"
    items {
      text: "I want to create a progressive web app named \"Quick Aid\". The app should satisfy the following problem statement:\n\"QuickAid \342\200\223 Smart First Aid Assistant\nProblem: In most emergencies, people don\342\200\231t know what immediate steps to take before reaching a hospital.\nSolution: Build a web/app that takes symptoms or emergencies (e.g., \342\200\234burn\342\200\235, \342\200\234choking\342\200\235, \342\200\234fracture\342\200\235) and gives voice-guided first-aid steps instantly.\"\n\nThe user should be able to enter the health problem either through text, voice or can choose from the common emergency issues buttons being displayed on the screen\nThe symptoms entered by the user should me collected and the instant first aid instructions need to be strictly taken from WHO instructions. The instructions generated should be generated in the text format and can turn into voice form if the user clicks on a button.\nThere should be an additional feature of GPS option to find the nearby hospitals by connecting with google-maps\nThe app should use Gemini in the background but should generate the first aid instructions only from WHO.\nProvide me fresh code for this such that I can run it in VS code in my laptop\nTry to keep the theme in blue color and a minimalist user interface with clean, responsive design components.\n"
    }
  }
}
