  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining Project: Quick Aid**\n\nI\'m solidifying the project\'s core - \"Quick Aid\", a progressive web app. Its function will be a smart first aid assistant. I\'m focusing on the input methods, specifically text and voice through the Web Speech API, for symptom or emergency descriptions. I\'m keen on how to best classify emergency types from user input.\n\n\n**Refining User Interface Elements**\n\nI\'m now integrating speech recognition with visual cues and graceful fallback options. I\'m focusing on user interface elements - like those common emergency buttons on screen. Next, I\'m integrating text-based WHO guidelines from Gemini, along with voice-guided steps via synthesis API. Finally, I\'m exploring Google Maps integration for nearby hospital location with a quick check on available skills.\n\n\n**Evaluating Architecture: Full-Stack**\n\nI\'ve determined that a full-stack architecture (Express + Vite) is necessary for this project. Specifically, I need server-side API routes for `/api/first-aid` to securely utilize the Gemini API, as well as Google Maps. Now, I\'m reviewing the `gemini-api` and `google-maps-platform` skills documents to understand integration requirements and determine how to proceed with implementation.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 4
      nanos: 573392435
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
