  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing Full-Stack Architecture**\n\nI\'m making excellent progress on designing the full-stack architecture. I\'m focusing on `server.ts` to build out the Express server. It will handle Vite serving during development and static files in production. The core API endpoint, `/api/first-aid`, is taking shape. It takes an emergency symptom as a query and calls the Gemini API `gemini-3.5-` model.\n\n\n**Refining System Instructions**\n\nI\'ve been meticulously crafting the system instructions for the Gemini API. My focus is on ensuring QuickAid delivers precise, actionable first aid advice. I\'ve formulated a system instruction emphasizing WHO guidelines, structured steps, and urgent warnings. It mandates a calm, authoritative tone, standardized output, and clear \"DOs\" and \"DON\'Ts\". I\'m meticulously eliminating any possibility of the system generating contradictory instructions or hallucinating.\n\n\n**Structuring Gemini Response**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the Gemini API\'s response schema. I realized `@google/genai` allows us to configure JSON output directly, which I\'m integrating into the system instructions. I\'m exploring the schema types within `@google/genai`, like `STRING`, `ARRAY`, `OBJECT`, etc., to structure the first aid advice output perfectly.\n\n\n**Implementing JSON Output**\n\nI\'ve successfully integrated the JSON output configuration for the Gemini API. The `responseSchema` is now defined using `Type.OBJECT`, `Type.STRING`, `Type.ARRAY`, and `Type.BOOLEAN` to enforce a structured response. This approach ensures the output is consistently typed, which I\'m very excited about. I\'m focusing on the client-side now, and I am exploring the use of the HTML5 Speech Synthesis API for audio output of the steps.\n\n\n**Adding Voice Integration**\n\nI\'m now integrating voice features for a richer user experience. The plan includes a \"Speak\" button that controls a TTS player for step-by-step guidance. I\'m designing controls for play/pause/stop/next/previous, with active step highlighting. This is important for a polished, accessible experience during emergencies. Additionally, I\'m exploring voice input options using the Web Speech API\'s `SpeechRecognition` for text-to-speech functionality.\n\n\n**Adding Voice Input**\n\nI\'m now focused on voice input. I\'m building a \"Tap to Speak\" button for the search input, with visual feedback for the listening state. It\'ll use the Web Speech API and have a fallback for unsupported browsers. I am also investigating the GPS hospital locator, and plan to use the user\'s location to connect with Google Maps for this feature.\n\n\n**Integrating Geolocation and Maps**\n\nI\'m now integrating geolocation with Google Maps. I\'m using the browser\'s `navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition` to fetch the user\'s location. This will feed an interactive map with the user\'s location and nearby hospital markers. I realized I have to ensure the `GOOGLE_MAPS_PLATFORM_KEY` is defined. This is resolved by the existing Vite setup, but it may require editing.\n\n\n**Configuring Vite for Maps**\n\nI\'m now integrating the Google Maps Platform API key within the Vite configuration. I\'ve realized I need to expose `process.env.GOOGLE_MAPS_PLATFORM_KEY` to the browser, as directed. I will define this within the `define` property of the `defineConfig` block, to ensure access. This is essential for the geolocation functionality to work with Google Maps.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 16
      nanos: 186555383
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
