  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Constructing the Server**\n\nOkay, I\'m now crafting the `/server.ts` file. My focus is integrating the `@google/genai` library within the Express server setup. The plan is to handle the `/api/first-aid` endpoint to generate structured WHO instructions. I\'m carefully writing that integration, making sure everything is well-defined.\n\n\n**Refining the Integration**\n\nI\'m now implementing the `@google/genai` library with the specific configurations, noting the `gemini-3.5-flash` model. I\'ve also pivoted to implementing lazy initialization, considering the best practice for API key management. This ensures smooth server startup even if the `GEMINI_API_KEY` isn\'t immediately available, while proactively generating helpful error messages.\n\n\n**Implementing Error Handling**\n\nI\'ve realized lazy initialization and robust error handling are critical for the `/api/first-aid` endpoint. Specifically, I\'m focusing on crafting a helpful JSON error response if the `GEMINI_API_KEY` is missing. This will be integrated into the server function. I\'m also planning the design of the instructions to be used to prompt the AI model.\n\n**Designing the Instructions**\n\nI\'m now crafting the system prompt. I\'m focused on ensuring it\'s WHO-compliant and produces structured JSON output for first-aid scenarios. The structure will have a title, severity assessment, steps, dos, and don\'ts, and will adhere strictly to WHO guidelines, with a key focus on only suggesting official recommendations.\n\n\n**Building the Hybrid Engine**\n\nI\'m now integrating a hybrid approach for the `/api/first-aid` endpoint. My plan is to have a pre-built, high-fidelity set of standard emergency instructions (like \"Choking,\" \"Heart Attack\") for immediate, zero-latency responses. For custom inputs, it will seamlessly leverage Gemini, ensuring speed for common cases and flexibility for complex scenarios. This hybrid model prioritizes speed in emergencies.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 14
      nanos: 741094695
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
