  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Reviewing UI Requirements**\n\nI\'m thrilled with the presets system; it\'s robust. Now I\'m shifting focus to the UI requirements, specifically how users input health problems. It\'s imperative that the system handles text, voice, and common emergency button selection for a flexible user experience. I\'m taking a look at `src/App.tsx` now to ensure seamless implementation.\n\n\n**Implementing Google Maps**\n\nI\'m now integrating Google Maps using `@vis.gl/react-google-maps` within `src/App.tsx`. I\'ve implemented the API key handling as specified, referencing `process.env.GOOGLE_MAPS_PLATFORM_KEY`, and created a fallback mechanism. A key validation check is in place; if the key is invalid, I\'ll provide a clear guide and mock map options.\n\n\n**Confirming Nearby Search**\n\nI\'ve confirmed `Place.searchNearby` functionality for hospital searches, satisfying the mapping requirement and the key\'s validation check implementation. When `hasValidKey` is true, an `<APIProvider>` with the API key renders the interactive `<Map>`.  Inside the map, I\'m now using this to search for nearby hospitals within a 5km radius, directly, which is perfect!\n\n\n**Adding Geolocation Functionality**\n\nI\'ve successfully integrated the geolocation API! If the browser provides the user\'s location, the map will be centered accordingly, displaying nearby hospitals with detailed distances and addresses. If geolocation is not given, the app will default to a predefined central city location. I\'ve also implemented options for the user to search their desired location! Furthermore, I\'ve listed the healthcare and controls icons I can import from `lucide-react`, and verified that the icons exist. I\'m excited with the progress!\n\n\n**Designing Modular Layout**\n\nI\'m now focusing on creating a beautiful, modular layout in `src/App.tsx`. I\'ve decided to create `/src/components/HospitalFinder.tsx` to handle the GPS search and Maps rendering, ensuring that the preset hospitals and map helpers are isolated, keeping things manageable and modular. The design is wonderful! The new component will render an educational screen for invalid API keys with a responsive mock hospital directory. I\'ll include real GPS coordinates and a deep link to Google Maps.\n\n\n**Simulating Hospital Data**\n\nI\'m now generating realistic mock hospital data! Using Haversine, I can simulate nearby hospitals based on the user\'s location with names like \"City General Hospital & Emergency Care.\" These mock hospitals will appear between 500m and 3km from the user, exactly like the real thing, with offsets!\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 32
      nanos: 310169335
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
