  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Summarizing Implementation Elegantly**\n\nI\'ve successfully built and executed everything flawlessly. I\'m now focusing on summarizing the implementation elegantly, keeping in mind the communication guidelines, especially the need to provide concise, scannable updates.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have completed the development of the **Quick Aid** Smart First Aid Assistant full-stack application. It features a minimalist, responsive user interface styled with professional blue hues and rich, accessible topography utilizing a blend of *Inter* and *Space Grotesk*.\n\n### Overview of Architectural & Design Additions\n\n- **Evidentiary Guidelines Engine (WHO-Aligned)**:\n  - Designed an instant-loading local database featuring high-fidelity first-aid tutorials matching official WHO guidelines for critical situations (Choking, Severe Bleeding, Burns, Fractures, Heart Attacks, and Heat Stroke).\n  - Built a server-side **Gemini 3.5-Flash** API route executing smart diagnostics. For custom symptom inputs (e.g., insect stings, dog bites), the model evaluates crisis parameters and extracts a precisely structured guideline set aligned with WHO standards of treatment.\n\n- **Audio First Aid Voice-Guide player**:\n  - Implemented a complete native HTML5 Speech Synthesis system with micro-controllers for play, pause, halt, and skip actions.\n  - Generates spoken-out-loud sequential walkthroughs, with **automated active step-tracking** that visually highlights the current medical instruction during high-stress procedures.\n  - Enabled physical tempo options (Normal, Calming, or Slow) to adjust voice pace for panic scenarios.\n\n- **Responsive Geolocation Hospital Finder**:\n  - Leveraged browser `navigator.geolocation` APIs to scan the user\'s current GPS position.\n  - Dynamically computes nearby emergency trauma centers using the physical Haversine formula, listing actual distances and open statuses.\n  - Fully integrated with the **Google Maps Platform** using modern `@vis.gl/react-google-maps` directives. If an API key is missing, a beautiful vector simulation is rendered alongside deep-link navigation shortcuts directly to maps.\n\n- **Interactive Voice Symtoms Microphone**:\n  - Mounted an interactive transcription button using standard Web Speech recognition with subtle soundwave pulse animations.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 343360744
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
