  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Developing Offline Access**\n\nI\'m focusing on the \"offline access\" feature for the \"Quick Aid\" PWA. My immediate goal is caching the critical first aid instructions and emergency contact functionality. This ensures the app remains usable even without an internet connection. I\'m prioritizing user experience and core functionality for seamless offline support.\n\n\n**Implementing Offline Functionality**\n\nI\'m now focusing on intelligent data syncing and offline state management. My plan involves a two-pronged approach. First, I want to use a service worker or the `navigator.onLine` API to handle offline/online states. Secondly, I need to choose local storage options like `localStorage` or `IndexedDB` to cache previous search queries and then queue them for sync when the connection is back. I\'ve also checked the existing project files\342\200\224`index.html`, `App.tsx`, `presets.ts`, `types.ts`, and `package.json`\342\200\224to ensure that no external libraries are needed.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Offline Usability**\n\nI am now structuring the offline experience for 100% usability. I\'m focusing on these steps: an \"Offline Mode\" badge based on `window.navigator.onLine`, custom query caching with `localStorage` or `IndexedDB`, and similar preset recommendations for new offline queries. I\'ll save unsynced queries in a \"Pending Sync Queue\" in `localStorage`, syncing them when the connection is restored.\n\n\n**Adding WHO Instructions**\n\nI\'m now focusing on pre-fetching the WHO instructions for offline access, a smart syncing approach. I\'m prioritizing service worker implementation for robust offline capabilities, especially in Vite projects. I\'m deciding whether to create a `public/sw.js` file or use an inline service worker for optimal efficiency. The project\'s file structure lacks a `public` directory, but Vite typically handles files there, so I\'ll check the directory listing in `/src` or `/` to finalize my decision on the service worker setup.\n\n\n**Checking Index.html for Service Worker**\n\nI\'ve decided to check `/index.html` to register a service worker. The existing file structure lacks a service worker implementation. I\'m considering adding a service worker to cache application assets. I also want to determine whether to manage API caching with a service worker or a custom React persistence layer, as the React level provides a more robust, stable approach.\n\n\n**Constructing App Manifest**\n\nI\'m now adding a `manifest.json` file to make this a true PWA. I\'ll inspect `/metadata.json` and similar files to inform the design. I plan to create a `/public/manifest.json` with icons, name, theme color, and the \"standalone\" display mode. I have confirmed that file creation handles directory generation, so that\'s a plus. I also am developing a quick design plan to add a dynamic connectivity and offline data cache.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 11
      nanos: 945959106
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
