  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing Offline Capability**\n\nI\'m focusing now on gracefully handling offline scenarios. My current goal is designing the application to behave beautifully when offline status is detected. I\'m starting by thinking about the variables and effects I\'ll need to add to `/src/App.tsx` to facilitate this.\n\n\n**Implementing Online-Offline State**\n\nI\'ve implemented `isOnline`, initializing it with the `navigator.onLine` status. I added global listeners for `\'online\'` and `\'offline\'` events to update this state. When we\'re back online, I\'ll automatically trigger a sync using `triggerBackgroundSync()`.\n\n\n**Managing Sync Queue**\n\nI\'ve added a `syncQueue` state, pulling data from local storage under the key \"quick-aid-sync-queue\". I\'m implementing `addToSyncQueue` to avoid duplicates and handle empty query strings, ensuring that any new queries are persisted in localStorage, and only added once to the queue. My focus is on robust local storage interaction.\n\n\n**Refining Sync Logic**\n\nI\'m now building out the `removeFromSyncQueue` function, ensuring it accurately removes entries from the queue in localStorage. I\'m also implementing the `triggerBackgroundSync` function to initiate data synchronization, checking for online status and non-empty queues.\n\n\n**Finalizing Sync Process**\n\nI\'ve got the auto-sync process completed now. I\'m handling the data posting to the API using a POST method with appropriate headers and stringified data. I\'m parsing the response to update our custom guides, remove items from the queue, and handle potential errors during the process. I am also updating the application state and local storage as needed.\n\n\n**Enhancing App Initialization**\n\nI\'ve added a useEffect hook to call `triggerBackgroundSync` upon app mount if the user is online. This ensures that the sync process begins automatically as soon as the application is ready and online. I\'m focusing on ensuring all the functionality I have is properly initialized and executed when the app first loads.\n\n\n\n**Optimizing Offline Search**\n\nI\'m now refining the offline search functionality, implementing a fallback strategy. When offline, if no preset or custom guide matches the query, I\'m displaying an error message about the limitations of offline search. I\'m focusing on providing the best possible user experience within offline constraints, including a clear explanation of limited functionality. I\'ve also implemented the offline banner display.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Offline Content**\n\nI\'m now integrating an automated mechanism to download standard WHO scenarios upon the next available online connection. I\'m prioritizing downloading essential guides, adding this step to my queue and including a safety message to review nearest matches while the download is pending, to ensure the user is protected if they don\'t have this.\n\n\n**Refining Scrolling & Error Handling**\n\nI\'ve integrated smooth scrolling to the results section after a brief delay for a smoother user experience, improving visibility. I\'ve also enhanced error handling to gracefully address connection issues, setting an appropriate error message and detailed steps. I\'ve added a fallback to offer sync or safe recovery guides in case of server errors.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 12
      nanos: 411245757
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
