    thinking: "**Refining the UI Elements**\n\nI\'m currently focused on the UI elements. I am updating the activeGuide badge, and working on rendering the pending sync queue within the Search Area. The sync message indicator will also be included in my modifications. The header is being tweaked, too.\n\n\n**Implementing Multi-Edit**\n\nI\'ve decided to leverage `multi_edit_file` for `/src/App.tsx`. The first chunk involves updating the header, specifically incorporating the Connectivity Status badge, which improves the UI.\n\n\n**Enhancing Status Indicator**\n\nI\'m now revising the connectivity status indicator. I\'ve updated the component\'s appearance to be more informative, incorporating visual cues for online/offline states. Also, the wording of the status indicator is improved. The goal is to provide a clearer user experience.\n\n\n**Improving the Offline Status**\n\nI am currently working on improving the offline status indicator. I\'m focusing on visual clarity, and I\'m updating its placement and styling. I\'ve also just implemented a sync notification block above the Announcement Hero. My goal is to enhance user awareness of the app\'s online/offline state.\n\n\n**Optimizing Layout and Status**\n\nI\'m now focusing on optimizing the layout. I\'m incorporating a split layout for the main app view, aiming for a cleaner interface. I\'m also implementing a background sync queue status indicator, using `AnimatePresence` for smoother transitions. The visual design is being improved with a shadow and rounded corners.\n\n\n**Integrating the Sync Queue**\n\nI\'m now integrating the offline sync queue display directly into the search area. I\'ve focused on displaying the sync message and pending queue count for improved visibility. I\'m also ensuring the visual design is consistent with existing elements.\n\n\n**Refining Search Interaction**\n\nI\'m now revising the search interactions, and I\'m updating the styles on the search button to indicate its functionality