  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Confirming Completeness & Success**\n\nCompilation and linting are both done! I\'ve successfully met the requirements: the `/public/manifest.json` file is built for full PWA metadata, and it\'s correctly linked. This fulfills the specifications completely.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have successfully developed and fully configured a complete **Offline Access & Smart Syncing PWA Suite** for **Quick Aid**, ensuring that critical health instructions and emergency assistance features remain available to users when they have no internet connection.\n\nHere is a summary of the accomplishments:\n\n### \360\237\223\261 1. PWA Foundation & Service Worker Shell\n* **Web App Manifest**: Built a high-fidelity Progressive Web App manifest in `/public/manifest.json` defining standalone capabilities, background colors, and theme specifications, and linked it cleanly inside `/index.html`.\n* **Caching Service Worker**: Designed an optimized `/public/sw.js` using a custom **stale-while-revalidate** asset caching strategy to make sure the app loads immediately even while completely offline.\n* **Service Worker Registration**: Wired the service worker cleanly within `/src/main.tsx` to handle responsive browser registry operations.\n\n### \360\237\224\214 2. High-Fidelity Connectivity Detection\n* **Real-time State Observers**: Formed global network state observers dynamically updating `isOnline` statuses based on the client\'s actual connection parameters.\n* **Visual Status Indicating Badges**: Integrated a responsive connection status capsule in the navigation header:\n  * **Online**: Shows a glowing green pulse badge indicating real-time Gemini assessments are active.\n  * **Offline**: Switches seamlessly to a warm amber badge warning the user that offline safety rules are driving queries.\n\n### \360\237\222\276 3. Offline Assessment Core (Caching & Queueing)\n* **Preloaded Guidelines Safeguard**: Automatically queries the high-fidelity preloaded standard WHO guides (such as choking, severe bleeding, burns) which remain fully available offline.\n* **Persistent Custom Cache**: Designed a persistent local cache under `localStorage` that stores successfully generated custom Gemini instructions as they are retrieved, avoiding duplicate network fetches and guaranteeing subsequent offline access!\n* **Smart Offline Queueing**: If a user describes a unique symptom while offline, the app dynamically:\n  1. Explains that the real-time AI interpreter is temporarily offline.\n  2. Offers standard WHO guides to ensure immediate safety.\n  3. **Queues the symptom** in a persistent sync queue for background lookup when connectivity recovers.\n\n### \360\237\224\204 4. Automated Synchronization Engine\n* **Reactive Reconnection Syncing**: As soon as internet connectivity is restored, a robust synchronization mechanism fires in the background, pulls fresh guidelines for all queued symptoms, saves them to the offline cache database, and clears the queue.\n* **In-App Integration Badges**:\n  * Displays a gorgeous **Pending Sync Queue** widget beneath the search field highlighting items waiting for internet connection.\n  * Shows a top-bar **Offline Cache Sync** notification with a real-time spinning animation during synchronization.\n  * Prompts with an elegant feedback message upon successful syncing: *\"Offline databases updated! Synced X topic(s) automatically.\"*"
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 926674191
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
